</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,817,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="201">
Female. Coloration (in 95% ethanol) (
<figureCitation box="[627,759,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,781,805]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,188,752]" captionTargetId="figure-27@7.[151,1436,181,757]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–38. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 34. Forewing; 35. Hindwing; 36. Head, frontal view; 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Habitus, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 34–38</figureCitation>
). Same as in male, but marking between median ocellus and anteclypeus paler. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[481,563,1662,1689]" captionStart="FIGURES 34–38" captionStartId="7.[151,264,781,805]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,188,752]" captionTargetId="figure-27@7.[151,1436,181,757]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 34–38. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 34. Forewing; 35. Hindwing; 36. Head, frontal view; 37. Habitus, lateral view; 38. Habitus, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) separated with numerous irregular pale brown markings and a V-shaped pale brown marking at proximal one-fifth. Morphology. Adult: Generally similar to male except for smaller compound eyes. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[332,464,1733,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,877,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-55@7.[151,1437,865,1659]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 39. Genitalia, dorsal view; 40. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 41. Genitalia, lateral view; 42. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 43–44. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 39–44</figureCitation>
): Epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[594,722,1733,1759]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,877,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-55@7.[151,1437,865,1659]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 39. Genitalia, dorsal view; 40. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 41. Genitalia, lateral view; 42. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 43–44. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 39–40</figureCitation>
) subtriangular, with a nearly H-shaped sclerotized area, distally rounded, antero-medially with setae. Paraproct (
<figureCitation box="[707,839,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,877,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-55@7.[151,1437,865,1659]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 39. Genitalia, dorsal view; 40. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 41. Genitalia, lateral view; 42. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 43–44. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 39–40</figureCitation>
) triangular, sensory field with about 38 trichobothria. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[396,526,1803,1829]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,877,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-55@7.[151,1437,865,1659]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 39. Genitalia, dorsal view; 40. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 41. Genitalia, lateral view; 42. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 43–44. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 43–44</figureCitation>
) with short and distally rounded egg guide, pigmented area slightly sclerotized, roughly T-shaped, apex nearly drop-shaped, pointed at tip, transverse region of pigmented area nearly dumbbelllike with numerous setae. Gonapophyses (
<figureCitation box="[631,765,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–44" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1682,1706]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,877,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-55@7.[151,1437,865,1659]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 39–44. Ceratostigma stagona sp. n., holotype female. 39. Genitalia, dorsal view; 40. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 41. Genitalia, lateral view; 42. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 43–44. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." pageId="5" pageNumber="201">Figs 41–42</figureCitation>
): Ventral valve slender, apex narrowed ventrally with short setae; dorsal valve broad, pointed at tip, with strongly sclerotized area at inner margin, ventro-distally with a slightly sclerotized area; external valve with a triangular posterior lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,817,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="201">
